DataElementConcept.preferredName: Secondary Acute Myeloid Leukemia Form National Cancer Institute Submission
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information submitted by printed or electronic document to National Cancer Institute staff regarding the advancement of myelodysplastic syndrome to acute myeloid leukemia.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: An acute myeloid leukemia secondary to a myelodysplastic syndrome or therapy-related.  (WHO, 2001) -- 2003:A printed or electronic document with spaces to be filled out.

Concepts.definition: An acute myeloid leukemia arising from prior myelodysplastic syndrome, myeloproliferative neoplasm, or myelodysplastic/myeloproliferative neoplasm, or as a result of previous exposure to alkylating agents or topoisomerase II inhibitors.
A printed or electronic document with spaces to be filled out.
